[2]
Date: Fri, 09 May 1997 18:19:58 -0400
From: Joe Shea (by way of Jack Woodall
)
I found this new information on a Caribbean-related health site,
apparently posted Wednesday [7 May 1997]:
Following recent statements in the press which reported an
outbreak of meningococcal meningitis in 3 cities near Santo
Domingo, CDC investigations have concluded that there has not
been an increase in the number of cases recorded. CDC is not
recommending that travel to the Dominican Republic be avoided,
nor that meningococcal vaccination be administered to travelers
to the country.
Posted 7 May 1997
--
Joe Shea
Editor-in-Chief
